{l s='Article 17 of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) includes the so-called right to be forgotten.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='This right means that in a number of cases organizations have to erase personal data if a data subject (the person whose data is processed) requests it.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='The right to be forgotten does not always apply.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='Only in the following situations is the right to be forgotten applicable:' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- No longer necessary.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='The organization no longer needs the personal data for the purposes for which the organization has collected them or for which the organization processes them.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- Withdraw permission.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='The person concerned has previously (explicitly) given permission to the organization for the use of his data, but now withdraws that consent.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- Objection.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='The person concerned objects to the processing. There is an absolute right of objection against direct marketing under Article 21 of the GDPR.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='And a relative right of objection if the rights of the person concerned outweigh the interest of the organization to process the personal data.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- Unlawful processing.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='The organization has processed the personal data unlawfully.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='For example, because there is no legal basis for the processing.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- The retention period.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='The organization is legally obliged to delete the data after a certain time.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- Children.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='The person concerned is younger than 16 years old and the personal data has been collected via an app or website.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) mentions a number of circumstances in which the right to forget does not apply:' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- The processing is necessary to exercise the right to freedom of expression and information.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='With this, the GDPR does justice to the principle that privacy and freedom of expression are equal fundamental rights.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- The organization processes the data because there is a legal obligation to do so.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- The organization processes the data to exercise public authority or a (statutory) task of general interest.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- The organization processes the data for a task of general interest in the field of public health.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- The organization must archive the data in the general interest.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='- The data are necessary for legal proceedings / lawsuit.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='The article offers organizations the opportunity to not respond to requests from people in special circumstances.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='They must then make a weighing of interests for that request, which shows that their interests (or the rights and freedoms of others) outweigh the privacy rights of the person concerned.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='For example, it is not the intention that those involved with an appeal to their rights erase traces of criminal behavior.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='Inform people about the right to be forgotten. People can send a request to be forgotten from the right to be forgotten account block.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='You can eighter automate this process, or you can give your approval first.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
